The paper deals with the recognition and characterization of point visibility graphs, which are a fundamental concept in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the complexity of the recognition problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper presents new properties of point visibility graphs, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
